-- Durant Has 28 Points to Lead Thunder to 104-92 Win Over Knicks
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-01-15T05:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-15/durant-has-28-points-to-lead-thunder-to-104-92-win-over-knicks.html
Kevin Durant  scored 28 points to
lead the Oklahoma City Thunder to their sixth straight win with
a 104-92 victory over the New York Knicks.  James Harden added 24 points and Russell Westbrook had 21
points last night for the Thunder who lead the National
Basketball Association’s Western Division with an 11-2 record.
Oklahoma City is one-half game behind the Chicago Bulls (12-2)
in the league.  Oklahoma City had a 70-47 halftime lead.  The Knicks, playing without an injured Carmelo Anthony,
were led by Amar’e Stoudemire,  Tyson Chandler  and reserve Toney Douglas who each had 14 points. New York lost its second
consecutive game.  The Knicks (6-6) are second in the Eastern Conference’s
Atlantic Division, three games behind the  Philadelphia 76ers  (9-
3).  To contact the reporter on this story:
